<paragraph id="8BCB9369FC1B0611FF29FD19A28A67F2" blockId="10.[136,1452,623,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64">
Note: This name was published in 1826, not 1824 as stated in some references. The 1824 copy of Hoffmannsegg’s work only treats 
<taxonomicName id="4C74E8EAFC1B0611FEC5FD3AA45867D5" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[337,528,695,721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cleomaceae" genus="Cleome" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="10" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis id="B9004F7BFC1B0611FEC5FD3AA45867D5" box="[337,528,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="64">Cleome violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is not clear what this name refers to, it has never seen usage in taxonomic treatments, and no 
<typeStatus id="54CF2DCBFC1B0611FEC9FD51A7C567F2" box="[349,397,732,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
material has been located to allow for definitive application of the name.
</paragraph>
